qaronN c
qaronN One's equal in age; syn. lidapN, (K,) or tirobN: with fet-h when relating to age, and with kesr when relating to fighting and the like. (Har, pp. 572,64.) ― -b2- qaronN, (JK, Msb,) or qaronN mina AlnRaAsi, (S,) [A generation of men;] people of one time (JK, * S, Ez-Zejjájee, Msb,) succeeding another qaron, (JK,) among whom is a prophet, or class of learned men, whether its years be many or few. (Ez-Zejjájee, Msb.) ― -b3- qaronN The part of the head of a human being which in an animal is the place whence the horn grows: (K:) or the side, (S,) or upper side, (K,) of the head: (S, K:) or [more exactly the temporal ridge (see SudogN) i. e.] the edge of the haAmap (which is the middle and main part of the head [i. e. of the cranium]), on the right and on the left. (Zj, in his “ Khalk el-Insán. ”) ― -b4- quruwnN of the head: see a verse cited voce xayRaTa. quruwnN of horses: see OajamRu. ― -b5- qaronN of a solid hoof: see jubRapN. ― -b6- qaronN of a desert, the most elevated part. (TA in art. jHf.) ― -b7- qaronu OaEofara, as meaning A spear-head, see OaEofaru. ― -b8- qaronN A pod, like that of the locust tree: pl. quruwnN. Occurring often in the work of AHn on plants, and in the TA, &c. See gaAfN. ― -b9- qaronN [A thing] in a she-camel, which is like the Eafal in a woman;
and which is cauterized with heated stones. (AA, TA, in art. Efl.) ― -b10- qaronN An issue of sweat: pl. quruwnN: see two ex. voce sanRa.
